HEADWORD: Cachexy
<hw>Ca*chex"y</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>cachexia</ets>, Gr.
<grk>kachexi`a</grk>; <grk>kako`s</grk> bad + <grk>"e`xis</grk>
condition.]</ety> <def>A condition of ill health and impairment of
nutrition due to impoverishment of the blood, esp. when caused by a
specific morbid process (as cancer or tubercle).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

